<reference id="em" xml:lang="en-us">
    <title><xmlelement>em</xmlelement></title>
    <shortdesc conkeyref="reuse-em/shortdesc"/>
    <prolog>
        <metadata>
            <keywords>
                <indexterm>emphasis
                    domain<indexterm><xmlelement>em</xmlelement></indexterm></indexterm>
            </keywords>
        </metadata>
    </prolog>
    <refbody>
    <section id="rendering-expectations">
      <title>Rendering expectations</title>
      <p>For Western languages, the content of the
          <xmlelement>em</xmlelement> element is typically rendered in an
        italic font.</p>
    </section>
    <section conkeyref="reuse-em/specialization-hierarchy"/>
        <section conkeyref="reuse-em/attributes" id="attributes"/>
        <example id="example" otherprops="examples">
      <title>Example</title>
            <p>The following code sample shows how the
          <xmlelement>em</xmlelement> element can be used to emphasize a
        phrase in a paragraph:</p>
            <codeblock>&lt;p>A good plan once adopted and put into execution <b>&lt;em>should not be 
abandoned&lt;/em></b> unless it becomes clear that it can not succeed.&lt;/p></codeblock>
            <!--<p>Emphasizing meaning within a sentence:</p><codeblock>&lt;p>What was previously called <b>&lt;em>block-level&lt;/em></b> content up to HTML 4.1 is now called 
                <b>&lt;em>flow&lt;/em></b> content in HTML5.&lt;/p></codeblock><p>Stressing the importance of a noun within a sentence:</p><p><codeblock>&lt;p>A <b>&lt;em>condenser&lt;/em></b> is an apparatus for condensing a large quantity of electricity 
                    on a comparatively small surface.&lt;/p></codeblock></p><p>Stressing the importance of a verb or actions within a sentence:</p><p><codeblock>To remove a message from a pigeon, first &lt;em>catch&lt;/em> the bird, then <b>&lt;em>hold&lt;/em></b> it 
                    in one hand, <b>&lt;em>extend&lt;/em></b> its leg, and &lt;em>remove&lt;/em> the message holder with the 
                    other hand.</codeblock></p>-->
        </example>
    </refbody>
